genMetaData

public ReconcileServlet.MetaData genMetaData()
Generates the MetaData which is returned for all non-query calls. The MetaData information is kept in a configuration file, which is a sqlite database on the server.

Returns:
A "MetaData" object which is converted to a JSON string with GSON

runQuery

Parameters:

Returns:
An ArrayList of Result objects, which will be returned and parsed into the JSON response

runQueries

public java.lang.String runQueries(javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest jsonReq)
This function parses apart queries requests and returns a string with the JSON response. It uses GSON to break apart the array of queries into individual ones, and it calls the match finder and manually puts together the response JSON string.

Parameters:
jsonReq - HttpServletRequest the original request with the JSON code
Returns:
A string with the JSON response to the request
